    public interface FormResultVisitor
extends Contexed
    This handles the mandatory types of FormResult. A FormResultVisitor should only implement view/display logic. Changes of model state should happen in a TransitionVisitor. Certain environments may define additional types and need to sub-class this interface. In this case the additional result types will need to cast the visitor to the sub-type. The prime example of this is WebFormResultVisitor which handles html-only result-types.
